The current treatments for Ebola typically involve receiving care in a hospital to manage the symptoms. This can include receiving fluids and electrolytes to maintain hydration, oxygen therapy, pain medication, antibiotics to combat any secondary infections and other medications or treatments to help manage the symptoms. There is currently no cure for ebola, but some treatments have shown promise in helping patients recover. Some of these treatments include the antiviral drug Remdesivir, the monoclonal antibody cocktail mAb114, and convalescent plasma therapy(in which plasma from a person who has recovered from ebola is given to a patient).
